## What is a server

A server is a physical or virtual machine that provides functionality to other programs or devices called clients.

## What is the role of the domain name

The role of the domain name is to provide text based names taht is easier to memorized than numerical addresses.

## What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com

CNAME

## What is the role of the web server

A web server stores, processess and delivers web pages to end users

## What is the role of the application server

Application server is responsible for handling the business logic and generating dynamic content for user

## What is the role of the database

The database is used for organizing and storing application data

## What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website

It uses HTTP (Hyper Text Traansfer Protocol)

## Issues are with this infrastructure:

### Single Point Of Failure:

The likelihood of SPOF in simple web infrastructure is high because there is no backup for the system.

### Downtime when maintenance needed (like deploying new code web server needs to be restarted)

During maintenance the system will be down.

### Cannot scale if too much incoming traffic

The simple web infrastructure can not scale.
